title: Developer ports One UI 4.1 to the Samsung Galaxy S9 and Galaxy Note 9
content:
Samsung has been quite generous with delivering the One UI 4.1 update. Aside from the flagships, the Korean OEM rolled out the new skin to affordable offerings like the Galaxy Note 10 Lite as well. That phone is powered by the Exynos 9810 processor, a 10nm octa-core SoC from 2018 that also powered the international

The post Developer ports One UI 4.1 to the Samsung Galaxy S9 and Galaxy Note 9 appeared first on xda-developers.
description: An unofficial port of One UI 4.1 is now available for the Exynos variants of the Samsung Galaxy S9, Galaxy S9 Plus, and the Galaxy Note 9.
